The chart itself is useful, but if you don't for the life of you know what the timeframe is youre looking at, the chart becomes useless. I suggest changing the default timescale to be longer (less tickmarks) to avoid the overlapping of dates.

We notice some pretty major performance drag when a user clones an issue that is being tracked in Greenhopper. What happens is that Greenhopper re-ranks all the issues, in our case a couple thousand issues, which puts a pretty major load on the system ('top' goes from a load 1 or 2 to a load of around 20) for about 2 minutes.  It also then takes about 2 minutes for the clone to complete.
It also kicks off an index optimization which is scary because then Lucene is locked up for a minute or 2 right in the middle of the day.

